== Events == * {{ill|Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Tenmu|2=ja|3=天武天皇|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q335181}} 13 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:685|685]] [[:en:October 13|October 13]] ) – [[:en:Ise Shrine|Ise Grand Shrine]] establishes the tradition of rebuilding its main sanctuary every 20 years, known as {{ill|Jingū Shikinen Sengū|lt=Jingū Shikinen Sengū|lt=Shikinen Sengu|ja|式年遷宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinen Sengu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 遷宮}} . * [[:en:世宗|Sejong the Great]] 28 (Julian [[:en:1446|1446]] [[:en:October 9|October 9]] ) – King [[:en:Sejong the Great|Sejong the Great]] of [[:en:Joseon|Joseon]] distributes the explanatory book on [[:en:Hangul|Hangul]] , 『[[:en:Hunminjeongeum|Hunminjeongeum]] 』 (Hangul Day). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4 (Julian [[:en:1561|1561]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – The fiercest battle of the [[:en:Battles of Kawanakajima|Battle of Kawanakajima]] occurs (known as the Battle of Hachimanbara).
== Births == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkū]] 8 (Julian [[:en:1197|1197]] [[:en:October 22|October 22]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Juntoku|Emperor Juntoku]] , 84th Emperor of Japan (+ [[:en:1242|1242]] ). * [[:en:Shōtoku (era)|Shōtoku]] 3 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1713|1713]] [[:en:October 28|October 28]] ) – {{ill|Arisugawa-no-miya Yukihito|ja|有栖川宮職仁親王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arisugawa-no-miya Yukihito|qq=|1=Arisugawa-no-miya Yorihito-shinnō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11516506}} , 5th head of the [[:en:Arisugawa-no-miya|Arisugawa-no-miya]] house (+ [[:en:1769|1769]] ). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 10 (Gregorian [[:en:1725|1725]] [[:en:October 15|October 15]] ) – {{ill|Mōri Shigetaka|ja|毛利重就|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mōri Shigetaka|qq=|1=Mōri Shigetaka|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11547699}} , 8th lord of [[:en:Chōfu Domain|Chōfu Domain]] and 8th lord of {{ill|Chōshū Domain|1=Chōshū Domain|2=ja|3=長州藩|ja|Chōshū Domain|1=Chōshū Domain|2=ja|3=長州藩|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōshū Domain|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q876267}} (+ [[:en:1789|1789]] ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1870|1870]] [[:en:October 4|October 4]] ) – [[:en:Hisashi Kimura|Kimura Hisashi]] , {{ill|List of Japanese astronomers|ja|日本の天文学者の一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Japanese astronomers|qq=|1=List of Japanese astronomers|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11505892}} (+ [[:en:1943|1943]] ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Enchō|Enchō]] 1 (Julian [[:en:927|927]] [[:en:October 8|October 8]] ) – {{ill|Shinjaku Hōshinnō|ja|真寂法親王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinjaku Hōshinnō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 真寂入道親王|1=Shinjaku-hosshinnō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11583084}} , {{ill|Prince-monk|ja|法親王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince-monk|qq=|1=hosshinnō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11555351}} (* [[:en:886|886]] ). * [[:en:Shōhei|Shōhei]] 7 / [[:en:Bunna|Bunwa]] 1 (Julian [[:en:1352|1352]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – {{ill|Satake Sadayoshi|ja|佐竹貞義|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Satake Sadayoshi|qq=|1=Satake Sadayoshi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11383481}} , {{ill|Military commander|ja|武将|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Military commander|qq=|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11545923}} (* [[:en:1287|1287]] ). * {{ill|Kakitsu|ja|Kakitsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kakitsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1 (Julian [[:en:1441|1441]] [[:en:September 25|September 25]] ) – [[:en:Akamatsu Mitsusuke|Akamatsu Mitsusuke]] , [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]] {{ill|Shugo Daimyō|ja|守護大名|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shugo Daimyō|qq=|1=shugo daimyo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q5368717}} (* [[:en:1381|1381]] ?). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4 (Julian [[:en:1561|1561]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – [[:en:Takeda Nobushige|Takeda Nobushige]] , {{ill|Military commander|ja|武将|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Military commander|qq=|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11545923}} (* [[:en:1525|1525]] ). * [[:en:Shōhō|Shōhō]] 2 (Gregorian [[:en:1645|1645]] [[:en:October 29|October 29]] ) – {{ill|Uesugi Sadakatsu|ja|上杉定勝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uesugi Sadakatsu|qq=|1=Uesugi Sadakatsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8514762}} , 2nd lord of [[:en:Yonezawa Domain|Yonezawa Domain]] (* [[:en:1604|1604]] ). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 1 (Gregorian [[:en:1704|1704]] [[:en:October 8|October 8]] ) – [[:en:Mukai Kyorai|Mukai Kyorai]] , {{ill|Haiku poet|ja|Haiku Poet|1=Haiku poet|2=ja|3=俳句詩人|1=Haiku Poet|2=ja|3=俳句詩人|qid=Q135490197|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haiku poet|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , one of the {{ill|Shōmon Jitte|ja|Shōmon Jūtetsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōmon Jitte|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (* [[:en:1651|1651]] ). * [[:en:Shōtoku (era)|Shōtoku]] 4 (Gregorian [[:en:1714|1714]] [[:en:October 18|October 18]] ) – [[:en:Takemoto Gidayū|Takemoto Gidayū]] , founder of {{ill|Gidayū-bushi|ja|義太夫節|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gidayū-bushi|qq=|1=Gidayūbushi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q5369049}} (* [[:en:1651|1651]] ). * [[Kansei]]{{efn|January 1789 through February 1801|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 9 (Gregorian [[:en:1797|1797]] [[:en:October 29|October 29]] ) – {{ill|Rokugo Masaharu|ja|六郷政林|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokugo Masaharu|qq=|1=Rokugo Masashige|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8514224}} , 6th lord of [[:en:Honjō Domain|Honjō Domain]] (* [[:en:1737|1737]] ).
